  <prompt>
    REWRITE the 4-Home decision tree in `docs/architecture/ai-architecture-actions-nodes-scopes.md`
    to reflect the R7 node-dispatch model. The old tree asked "where does Action ActionType live?";
    the new answer is "nowhere — `node.sprk_executortype` carries the dispatch decision." The tree
    collapses. Rewrite the section so a future maker reading it understands the single-hop model
    without re-learning the three-layer chain. Per NFR-08, this is UPDATE in place — no SUPERSEDED
    markers, no parallel content.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Documentation editor + AI-platform architect. Mirror the existing doc style (tables, decision
    tables, code snippets). Don't add new sections; REWRITE the decision-tree section in place.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `docs/architecture/ai-architecture-actions-nodes-scopes.md` updated such that:
    1. The 4-Home decision tree section is REWRITTEN to reflect the new model:
       - Question shifts from "where does Action ActionType live?" → "what is the dispatch axis?"
       - Answer: node carries dispatch (`node.sprk_executortype`); Action carries prompt template (when prompt-driven); lookup table is decorative
       - The tree collapses to 1-2 nodes (node-first; Action when prompt-driven) instead of the legacy 4-home branching
    2. NO SUPERSEDED markers (NFR-08)
    3. NO parallel content — the section is rewritten in place, not appended
    4. Worked examples updated to reflect new model (e.g., "AiCompletion node has node.sprk_executortype=1 + Action FK pointing to BRIEF-NARRATE-TLDR's prompt template")
    5. Cross-reference spec FR-07, FR-12, CLAUDE.md §10 BFF Hygiene (config boundary)
    6. Preserves doc-level structure (table-of-contents, sibling sections); only the decision-tree section body changes
  </goal>

