  <context>
    <background>
      Pre-R7, the doc explained that a node's dispatch axis could be inferred from one of four
      "homes": Node Type Choice column, Action ActionType lookup, Action's executor field on the
      lookup row, or structural fallback. R7 collapses that — the only home is
      `node.sprk_executortype`. The decision-tree section is the prime artifact authors reach for
      when learning where things live; rewriting it sets the new mental model correctly.
    </background>
