    <step order="4" name="Draft the rewritten section">
      Write the new section. Structure:
      - **Section heading** (preserve or adjust per doc convention)
      - **One-sentence framing**: "Dispatch reads `node.sprk_executortype` directly. Action FK is optional (required only for prompt-driven executors)."
      - **Decision table** (2 columns: "What you need to express" → "Where it lives"):
        | Need | Lives on |
        |---|---|
        | Which executor handles the node | `node.sprk_executortype` (Choice; required) |
        | Prompt template (when prompt-driven) | Action via `node.sprk_actionid` (Lookup; optional) |
        | Maker categorization / browsing | `sprk_analysisactiontype` lookup table (decorative; advisory only) |
      - **Two worked examples**: (1) AiCompletion node (node.sprk_executortype=1 + Action FK with prompt); (2) Condition node (node.sprk_executortype=30, no Action FK)
      - **Cross-references**: cite spec FR-07, FR-12, CLAUDE.md §10 BFF Hygiene config boundary
    </step>
